						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">jwdonal wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">While the SPC-700 processor core does have interrupt support, neither the IRQ nor NMI pins are brought out to any of the pins on the S-SMP wrapper. They are both tied off to their inactive levels internally (i.e. inside the S-SMP chip). You can see the entire schematic and pinout of the device <a href="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/36237540/SNES/jwdonal/schematics/snes_schematic.zip" class="postlink">here</a>. So what/where is this &quot;IRQ line&quot; that you're hooking up to?</div><br /><br />Oh, darn. Was hoping they left the pin on the chip but just tied to ground or something.<br /><br />So ... anyone want to try partial decapping and tapping the line directly on the die with a tungsten needle?</div>

